## üì¶ Installation

### Option A ‚Äî Automatic (Recommended)

Run this to install the dependency and automatically save the hash:

```bash
zig fetch --save https://github.com/muhammad-fiaz/zon.zig/archive/refs/tags/0.0.3.tar.gz
```

After running, Zig updates your `build.zig.zon` with something like:

```zig
.dependencies = .{
    .zon = .{
        .url = "https://github.com/muhammad-fiaz/zon.zig/archive/refs/tags/0.0.3.tar.gz",
        .hash = "zon-0.0.3-9stQDcuXAwB6ocoQ7hTdIabG-jRAsl7K2N36zwzndGPh",
    },
},
```

Then in your `build.zig`:

```zig
const zon_dep = b.dependency("zon", .{
    .target = target,
    .optimize = optimize,
});
exe.root_module.addImport("zon", zon_dep.module("zon"));
```

### Option B ‚Äî Manual

```bash
zig fetch --hash https://github.com/muhammad-fiaz/zon.zig/archive/refs/tags/0.0.3.tar.gz
```

Copy that hash into:

```zig
.hash = "<your_hash_here>" // which is zon-0.0.3-9stQDcuXAwB6ocoQ7hTdIabG-jRAsl7K2N36zwzndGPh
```

## ‚ú® Quick Start

```zig
const std = @import("std");
const zon = @import("zon");

pub fn main() !void {
    var gpa = std.heap.GeneralPurposeAllocator(.{}){};
    defer _ = gpa.deinit();
    const allocator = gpa.allocator();

    var doc = zon.create(allocator);
    defer doc.deinit();

    try doc.setString("name", "myapp");
    try doc.setString("version", "1.0.0");
    try doc.setInt("port", 8080);

    try doc.saveAs("config.zon");
}
```

