| Platform | Architecture | File |
|----------|--------------|------|
| Windows | x86_64 | [zon-x86_64-windows.lib](https://github.com/muhammad-fiaz/zon.zig/releases/download/0.0.3/zon-x86_64-windows.lib) |
| Windows | x86 | [zon-x86-windows.lib](https://github.com/muhammad-fiaz/zon.zig/releases/download/0.0.3/zon-x86-windows.lib) |
| Linux | x86_64 | [libzon-x86_64-linux.a](https://github.com/muhammad-fiaz/zon.zig/releases/download/0.0.3/libzon-x86_64-linux.a) |
| Linux | x86 | [libzon-x86-linux.a](https://github.com/muhammad-fiaz/zon.zig/releases/download/0.0.3/libzon-x86-linux.a) |
| Linux | aarch64 (ARM64) | [libzon-aarch64-linux.a](https://github.com/muhammad-fiaz/zon.zig/releases/download/0.0.3/libzon-aarch64-linux.a) |
| macOS | x86_64 (Intel) | [libzon-x86_64-macos.a](https://github.com/muhammad-fiaz/zon.zig/releases/download/0.0.3/libzon-x86_64-macos.a) |
| macOS | aarch64 (Apple Silicon) | [libzon-aarch64-macos.a](https://github.com/muhammad-fiaz/zon.zig/releases/download/0.0.3/libzon-aarch64-macos.a) |
| Bare Metal | x86_64 | [libzon-x86_64-freestanding.a](https://github.com/muhammad-fiaz/zon.zig/releases/download/0.0.3/libzon-x86_64-freestanding.a) |
| Bare Metal | x86 | [libzon-x86-freestanding.a](https://github.com/muhammad-fiaz/zon.zig/releases/download/0.0.3/libzon-x86-freestanding.a) |
| Bare Metal | aarch64 | [libzon-aarch64-freestanding.a](https://github.com/muhammad-fiaz/zon.zig/releases/download/0.0.3/libzon-aarch64-freestanding.a) |
| Bare Metal | RISC-V 64 | [libzon-riscv64-freestanding.a](https://github.com/muhammad-fiaz/zon.zig/releases/download/0.0.3/libzon-riscv64-freestanding.a) |
| Bare Metal | ARM | [libzon-arm-freestanding.a](https://github.com/muhammad-fiaz/zon.zig/releases/download/0.0.3/libzon-arm-freestanding.a) |

### üõ†Ô∏è Using Prebuilt Libraries

1. Download the library for your platform.
2. Place it in your project (e.g., in a `libs/` folder).
3. Update your `build.zig`:

```zig
exe.addLibraryPath(b.path("libs"));
exe.linkSystemLibrary("zon");
```

